ines.\n1 After the CAB awarded\na Northeast a New York-Miami\n3 route last year two other air\nlines. National and Eastern.\n,r challenged Northeast's fitness\n4 in the light of the Hughes-TWA\n6 relationship They said Mr.\nHughes had acquired 11 per\ncent of the outstanding shares\nof Atlas common stock through\nthe 1956 merger of RKO Pic\ntures Corp. with Atlas.\nIn approving Northeast's\nMiami route award last year.\nthe CAB noted Mr. Hughes had\ncommitted himself irrevocably\nto permit Floyd B. Odium, Atlas\n_ president, to vote Mr. Hughes'\nstock in Atlas until Mr. Hughes\nj had disposed of it.\nt Dry Milk Sets Record\n1 MILWAUKEE \u2014The Nation's\n1 production of nonfat dry milk\n1 last year climbed to 1.484.00(V\n--000 pounds, the highest on rec\nord.\nt\n~~DIVIDENDS\nI NEW YORK. Oct J tr\u2014Divi\ndends announced\nInitial\n9 Pa- Btk of Pav\nRat*, fiod \"cord abir\nShawln WAP new 17c 10-16 ]|.\u201d6\nDo A new 33+c lli-lsi 11-16\nSleek\nKattar Julius 10-21 ,1-ls\ne Increased\nNor Chore O 111 22to* 11-s i;.\u00bb\nC Reaular\nHoover B A- Bear 26c 111-lit 10-31\nLanaton Induat 16c Q 10-,'(n n-|-\u00ab\n,f Crown f *_6 Ltd Sue Q li\u2019-lS 11-16\nManrfield T A R lute 10-7 10-10\nNorthweat Alrlln 20c 10-10 11-i\no f rr Bros A Co 76c Q 10-11\n0 Sareent A Co 26c Q 10-4 lIM6\n-:W\u00bb rn er C\u00b0 Stic Q l\u201d-4 10-li\nSoc Q l\u201d-i\u00bb n.\u00bb\nB Bilker Hill ...15c __ KMii ||.f>\n\u00abl De Vtlblsa C\u00ab .Stic Q 10-11 10-21\nI Hart sch A Mark 40c 10-70 11-72\n1 ur\u2018\u00ab. SSS81S:l\u00abl?;6\ny N. Y. PRODUCE\nC\nNEW YORK. Oct 1 <f*v \u00bb\u00dcBDA'.\nPrICM uoclianaed. Ra-\nV 1 Refill* 4-\u00bb Pr UnCh ,Wd\nH w\u00dfalaaata eea price, were steady\nReceipt. 20.00\". New York spot olio\nn tallona follow Midwestern: Mixed col\nors. Extra. 14H.50 ibai 50-62 .xtras\nl*Re 145-40 Ibai 40-50: extras nie\nrj!'i m 3,\u00bb-35'4 -tanderds hirie 37 1\nWhite*, extras\nAl-53'.i extras larae 145-'\n40 Ibai 411-51: extras medium 35*30\nBrowns, eatras 140-50 Ibai 5